  <h1>The Administrator</h1>
  <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>This project was something that was inspired by my past as a consultant and how that meant frequent office visits. I had not been near an office since the beginning of quarantine in San Francisco. I was wondering how a new office guest software would handle guests in the dynamic post pandemic environment, and ended up with what I pictured would be the requirement for what an office would need.</p>
    <h2>Software</h2>
    <p>This project was the capstone project for my coursework at General Assembly. It was built using the MERN stack and utilizes Mongo Atlas as a database and Heroku for a back end Node server.</p>
    <h2>Learning and Growth</h2>
    <p>I really enjoyed learning about several aspects of the code that I worked with over the course of this project. I'm also proud of how uniform I was able to get the application. Things that I learned in this project include: </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Twilio SMS</li>
      <li>React Portals</li>
      <li>React-Bootstrap</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Twilio SMS</h3>
    <p>After struggling with email notifications, I decided to integrate the Twilio API to send SMS messages which was a good first step in getting this application where I want it to be in terms of engaging its users. I'm glad I did. The Twilio API is well documented and has several examples to get you started. It also has a free trial period that helps you decide if it is what you are looking to add to your application! Super inviting and easy to envision using, 10/10 experience.</p>

