    <p>As this was my first solo project since my first project in class, I really wanted to take the time and make sure everything was on the same level and looked cohesive. As I learned, there is no better way to accomplish this complete feeling than implementing a styling framework to tie everything together into a neat stylistic motif. In addition, I also learned about color accessibility and found a <a href='https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/'>tool</a>  to make sure that colors you are using are easy to read for those who may have color blindness or other vision impairments. I would love to integrate ideas that are on the same train of thought of accessibility in my future work.</p>
